# BROWSER-core.md - Bluesky Global Rules & Shared Patterns


**Navigate:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://bsky.app/..."}' 2>&1
```

**Selectors:** Use evaluate to find and interact with all elements.

**Tool:** `evaluate` for all interaction — extract data, check states, type text, click buttons.

**Selectors:**
- Post containers: `div[role="link"]` — each post is wrapped in one, use as boundary
- Post links: `a[href*="/post/"]` — extract author/postId from URL pattern `/profile/{handle}/post/{id}`
- Reply button (search/feed): `button[aria-label*="Reply"]` — label format: `"Reply (N replies)"`
- Like button: `button[aria-label*="Like"]` — label format: `"Like (N likes)"`
- Repost button: `button[aria-label="Repost or quote post"]`
- Compose reply (post page): `button[aria-label="Compose reply"]`
- Dialog: `[role="dialog"]`
- Textbox: `[role="textbox"][contenteditable="true"]`
- Submit reply: `button[aria-label="Publish reply"]` (text: "Reply")
- Submit post/quote: `button[aria-label="Publish post"]` (text: "Post")
- Follow button: `button` with text "Follow" / "Following"
- Tabs (search): `div[role="tab"]` or `button[role="tab"]` — "Top", "Latest", "People", "Feeds"

**Wait pattern:** Embed waits at START of next evaluate: `async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); ... }`

**Bluesky DOM notes:**
- Bluesky uses React with accessible markup — `button`, `role="link"`, `aria-label` attributes are reliable
- NO `<article>` tags — use `div[role="link"]` as post container
- Class names are auto-generated (e.g., `css-g5y9jx`) — NEVER use them
- Engagement counts are in button aria-labels, NOT in visible text (text just shows the number)
- Menu items after repost click use `div[role="menuitem"]`

